                     ROBERT TURNER (44)






                           PLEADED GUILTY
                      to falsifying certain books of the 

                        Chelsea Savings Bank, his masters; 
                  also 


                     to embezzling £35 10s.; 
                  also 


                     to stealing £200; and within six months £100, and within six months £200; 
                  also 


                     to stealing £100, £100, and £100; 
                  also 


                     £250, £100, and £160; 
                  also 


                     £198 and £100 of his said masters. (MR. C. MATHEWS, for the prosecution, stated that the prisoner's defalcations amounted to £500).—



                     Seven Years' Penal Servitude.
